Key Match Events: Australia beat South Africa to reach World Cup final
Travis Head scored 62 runs off 48 balls and was named player of the match
South Africa slumped to 24-4 under grey skies
Post-Match Reflections: Pat Cummins expressed excitement about reaching the final and playing in India
Temba Bavuma acknowledged South Africa's resilience and character
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was tense and went down to the wire
The conditions were helpful for bowling, with the ball swinging around
Others: The final will be against unbeaten India
